{"updated_at": {"date": {"d": "24", "m": "03", "Y": "2026"}, "time": {"H": "10", "M": "39", "S": "22"}}, "news": [{"title": "India\u2019s flex office stock crosses 100 million sq ft, demand driven by IT, GCCs: Report", "para": "Crossing the 100 million sq ft mark, India's flexible office space has witnessed remarkable expansion in just five years. At the helm is Bengaluru, boasting the highest concentration of flexible work environments. The surge in demand is primarily fueled by IT, technology, and BFSI industries, with international corporations taking the lead in space absorption.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/commercial/indias-flex-office-stock-crosses-100-million-sq-ft-demand-driven-by-it-gccs-report/129772481?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-272704/129772481.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "commercial"}, {"title": "ASK Property Fund exits \u20b9650 crore investment in Mahagun\u2019s Noida project", "para": "ASK Property Fund has successfully exited its investment in a Mahagun Group residential project in Noida. The fund generated a 21% IRR and a 2.1x multiple from this deal. Additionally, ASK Property Fund completed a full exit from its 2018 debt fund, achieving an investment multiple of 1.83x.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/residential/ask-property-fund-exits-650-crore-investment-in-mahaguns-noida-project/129772340?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-118822/129772340.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "residential"}, {"title": "Telangana HC pulls up HYDRAA for taking over plot in Hayathnagar", "para": "The Hyderabad High Court has again criticized HYDRAA for allegedly seizing a 650 square yard plot, deeming the action unconstitutional. Justice NV Shravan Kumar expressed shock at the agency's interference in sub judice property disputes, noting a lack of change in HYDRAA's attitude despite previous court orders. The court has sought a response from HYDRAA by March 25.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/regulatory/telangana-high-court-rebukes-hydraa-over-forcible-property-takeover-in-hayathnagar/129765538?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-20680/129765538.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "regulatory"}]}